            "id": 1,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This study describes the inheritance of a defect in pyrimidine catabolism and its association with drug-induced toxicity in a patient",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "receiving 5-fluorouracil ( FUra ) as adjuvant chemotherapy for breast carcinoma . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The study population included the affected patient ( proband ) , nine of her blood relatives , and seven healthy volunteers . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "The activity of dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase ( DPD ) , the initial enzyme of pyrimidine ( and FUra ) catabolism , in peripheral blood mononuclear cells was measured in each subject by a specific radiometric assay",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "using FUra as the substrate . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The proband had no detectable DPD activity . <S>",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "When enzyme levels in the proband and relatives were compared with that in controls ,",
            "relation": "TEMPORAL"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "an autosomal recessive pattern of inheritance was demonstrated . <S>",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "This is the third patient with severe FUra toxicity",
            "relation": "ADDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "secondary to an alteration in pyrimidine catabolism",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "and the second from our clinic population",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "suggesting that the frequency of this genetic defect may be greater than previously thought . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Monitoring DPD activity may be important in the management of patients",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "experiencing severe toxicity",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "secondary to FUra chemotherapy . <S>",
